{"content":"---\ntitle: \"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"csharp\"\n  - \"vb\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"adorners [WPF], removing\"\nms.assetid: 97cf4d9f-0596-429e-8526-32a30aa4ae99\n---\n# How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element\nThis example shows how to programmatically remove a specific adorner from a specified <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>.  \n  \n## Example  \n This verbose code example removes the first adorner in the array of adorners returned by <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdorners%2A>.  This example happens to retrieve the adorners on a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> named *myTextBox*.  If the element specified in the call to <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdorners%2A> has no adorners, `null` is returned.  This code explicitly checks for a null array, and is best suited for applications where a null array is expected to be relatively common.  \n  \n [!code-csharp[AdornersMiscCode#_RemoveSpecificAdornerLong](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/AdornersMiscCode/CSharp/Window1.xaml.cs#_removespecificadornerlong)]\n [!code-vb[AdornersMiscCode#_RemoveSpecificAdornerLong](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_Wpf/AdornersMiscCode/visualbasic/window1.xaml.vb#_removespecificadornerlong)]  \n  \n## Example  \n This condensed code example is functionally equivalent to the verbose example shown above. This code does not explicitly check for a null array, so it is possible that a <xref:System.NullReferenceException> exception may be raised.  This code is best suited for applications where a null array is expected to be rare.  \n  \n [!code-csharp[AdornersMiscCode#_RemoveSpecificAdornerShort](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/AdornersMiscCode/CSharp/Window1.xaml.cs#_removespecificadornershort)]\n [!code-vb[AdornersMiscCode#_RemoveSpecificAdornerShort](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_Wpf/AdornersMiscCode/visualbasic/window1.xaml.vb#_removespecificadornershort)]  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [Adorners Overview](adorners-overview.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,212],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"csharp\"\n  - \"vb\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"adorners [WPF], removing\"\nms.assetid: 97cf4d9f-0596-429e-8526-32a30aa4ae99","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element","nodes":[{"pos":[0,41],"content":"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element","pos":[0,41]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[219,260],"content":"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element","linkify":"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Remove an Adorner from an Element","pos":[0,41]}]},{"pos":[261,379],"content":"This example shows how to programmatically remove a specific adorner from a specified <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph>.","source":"This example shows how to programmatically remove a specific adorner from a specified <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>."},{"pos":[388,395],"content":"Example","linkify":"Example","nodes":[{"content":"Example","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"This verbose code example removes the first adorner in the array of adorners returned by <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdorners%2A&gt;</ph>.","pos":[399,548],"source":"This verbose code example removes the first adorner in the array of adorners returned by <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdorners%2A>."},{"content":"This example happens to retrieve the adorners on a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph> named <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>myTextBox<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.","pos":[550,651],"source":"  This example happens to retrieve the adorners on a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> named *myTextBox*."},{"content":"If the element specified in the call to